1
00:00:00,876 --> 00:00:05,923
[ MUSIC ]

2
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:13,597
ALL CLEAR AHEAD, CAPTAIN.

3
00:00:13,597 --> 00:00:15,975
SENSORS INDICATE ZERO REGISTER.

4
00:00:15,975 --> 00:00:17,685
FORWARD READINGS, MR. SPOCK.

5
00:00:17,685 --> 00:00:19,728
BAROMETRIC READING,
NO SIGNIFICANCE CHANGE,

6
00:00:19,728 --> 00:00:21,313
ZERO SPACE DENSITY.

7
00:00:21,313 --> 00:00:23,941
AHEAD WARP FACTOR THREE,
MR. SULU.

8
00:00:23,941 --> 00:00:25,567
COLONY BETA SIX
WANTS THEIR SUPPLIES.

9
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:28,403
WE'LL GET ACROSS THIS VOID
IN A HURRY.

10
00:00:28,403 --> 00:00:30,155
VOID, STAR DESERT.

11
00:00:30,155 --> 00:00:34,409
THE WORD CONJURES UP PICTURES
OF DUNES, OASES, MIRAGES.

12
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:36,495
SUNLIGHT, PALM TREES.

13
00:00:36,495 --> 00:00:39,665
WE'RE 900 LIGHT YEARS
FROM THAT KIND OF DESERT, BONES.

14
00:00:39,665 --> 00:00:41,959
THE PRECISE MEANING
OF THE WORD DESERT

15
00:00:41,959 --> 00:00:45,004
IS A WATERLESS,
BARREN WASTELAND.

16
00:00:45,004 --> 00:00:47,422
I FAIL TO UNDERSTAND
YOUR ROMANTIC NOSTALGIA

17
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:49,299
FOR SUCH A PLACE.

18
00:00:49,299 --> 00:00:51,593
DOESN'T SURPRISE ME, MR. SPOCK.

19
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:54,179
I CAN'T IMAGINE A MIRAGE
EVER DISTURBING

20
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:57,599
THOSE MATHEMATICALLY PERFECT
BRAIN WAVES OF YOURS.

21
00:00:57,599 --> 00:00:59,643
THANK YOU, DR. McCOY.

22
00:00:59,643 --> 00:01:03,104
MOVING ON SCHEDULE
INTO QUADRANT 904,

23
00:01:03,104 --> 00:01:06,817
BETA SIX IS EIGHT DAYS DISTANT.

24
00:01:06,817 --> 00:01:07,735
SOMETHING, MR. SPOCK?

25
00:01:07,735 --> 00:01:08,861
UNUSUAL, CAPTAIN.

26
00:01:08,861 --> 00:01:13,532
I'M NOW GETTING A SIZABLE
SPACE DISPLACEMENT READING.

27
00:01:13,532 --> 00:01:15,075
CAN YOU VERIFY THAT, NAVIGATOR?

28
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:17,244
NO, SIR.
FORWARD SWEEPS ARE NEGATIVE.

29
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:19,246
WAIT! VERIFIED, SIR.

30
00:01:19,246 --> 00:01:20,706
WE MUST BE IN SOME SORT
OF LIGHT WARP

31
00:01:20,706 --> 00:01:22,249
OR WE WOULD HAVE PICKED IT UP
EARLIER.

32
00:01:22,249 --> 00:01:28,505
PUT IT ON VISUAL.

33
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:34,135
IRON SILICA BODY, PLANET SIZE,
MAGNITUDE 1E.

34
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:36,055
WE'LL BE PASSING CLOSE.

35
00:01:36,055 --> 00:01:39,307
INCONCEIVABLE THIS BODY HAS GONE
UNNOTED ON ALL OUR RECORDS.

36
00:01:39,307 --> 00:01:43,520
AND YET HERE IT IS.
NO TIME TO INVESTIGATE.

37
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:46,523
SCIENCE STATIONS
GATHER DATA FOR COMPUTER BANKS.

38
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:49,651
UHURA, NOTIFY THE DISCOVERY
ON SUBSPACE RADIO.

39
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:52,446
STRONG INTERFERENCE ON SUBSPACE,
CAPTAIN.

40
00:01:52,446 --> 00:01:54,865
THE PLANET MUST BE
A NATURAL RADIO SOURCE.

41
00:01:54,865 --> 00:01:56,491
LET'S GET OUT OF ITS RANGE.

42
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:59,119
VEER 40 DEGREES TO STARBOARD,
MR. SULU.

43
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:05,500
40 DEGREES.

44
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:12,007
SULU!

45
00:02:12,007 --> 00:02:14,551
MR. SPOCK, THEY'RE GONE!

46
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:20,223
EMERGENCY! FULL REVERSE POWER!

47
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:24,895
[ MUSIC ]

48
00:02:24,895 --> 00:02:28,857
SPACE, THE FINAL FRONTIER.

49
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:32,569
THESE ARE THE VOYAGES
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

50
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:37,658
ITS FIVE-YEAR MISSION:
TO EXPLORE STRANGE, NEW WORLDS,

51
00:02:37,658 --> 00:02:41,620
TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE
AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS,

52
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:46,792
TO BOLDLY GO
WHERE NO MAN HAS GONE BEFORE.

53
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:22,911
SHIP'S LOG, STARDATE 2124.5.

54
00:03:22,911 --> 00:03:25,873
FIRST OFFICER SPOCK REPORTING
FOR CAPTAIN JAMES KIRK.

55
00:03:25,873 --> 00:03:28,291
WE ARE ORBITING
THE LONE UNRECORDED PLANET

56
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:29,918
IN THE STAR DESERT.

57
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:33,047
FOR FOUR HOURS, WE HAVE MADE
EVERY POSSIBLE INSTRUMENT SWEEP,

58
00:03:33,047 --> 00:03:35,174
BUT CAPTAIN KIRK
AND HELMSMAN SULU

59
00:03:35,174 --> 00:03:36,758
REMAIN UNACCOUNTED FOR.

60
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:39,011
I HAVE PLACED THE SHIP
ON RED ALERT.

61
00:03:39,011 --> 00:03:41,096
WE'VE SEARCHED AGAIN
FROM STEM TO STERN.

62
00:03:41,096 --> 00:03:42,305
IF THEY'RE NOT DOWN
ON THAT PLANET,

63
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:43,223
THEY'RE NOWHERE.

64
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,266
NO SIGN OF HUMAN LIFE
ON THE SURFACE, SIR,

65
00:03:45,266 --> 00:03:48,062
UNLESS THE INSTRUMENTS
AREN'T FUNCTIONING.

66
00:03:48,062 --> 00:03:52,273
FUNCTION IS NORMAL.
CONTINUE SENSOR SWEEPS.

67
00:03:52,273 --> 00:03:54,442
LIEUTENANT UHURA,
HAVE YOU CHECKED ALL WAVE BANDS?

68
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:56,653
ALL OF THEM, MR. SPOCK.
NO RESPONSE.

69
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:58,572
WITH DUE RESPECT, SIR,
REQUEST PERMISSION

70
00:03:58,572 --> 00:03:59,948
TO TRANSPORT TO THE SURFACE
IMMEDIATELY

71
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,282
AND CARRY OUT SEARCH.

72
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:05,579
I SECOND DESALLE'S REQUEST.
WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?

73
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:07,664
THE DECISION WILL BE MINE,
DOCTOR.

74
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:10,458
I HAVE THE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR YOUR SAFETY.

75
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:12,878
MR. JAEGER, DESCRIBE
YOUR GEOPHYSICAL FINDINGS

76
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:14,295
FOR THE SURFACE BELOW.

77
00:04:14,295 --> 00:04:17,674
NO DETECTABLE SOIL
OR VEGETATION, EXTREMELY HOT,

78
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:20,510
TOXIC ATMOSPHERE
SWEPT BY TORNADIC STORMS,

79
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:24,223
CONTINUOUS VOLCANIC ERUPTIONS,
DEADLY TO ANY LIFE FORM

80
00:04:24,223 --> 00:04:25,933
SUCH AS WE KNOW IT
WITHOUT OXYGEN

81
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:27,935
AND LIFE SUPPORT SYSTEMS.

82
00:04:27,935 --> 00:04:30,520
ESTIMATE SURVIVAL TIME
OF TWO UNPROTECTED INDIVIDUALS

83
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,522
DOWN THERE.

84
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:34,482
NOT VERY LONG.

85
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:39,529
MR. SPOCK, LOOK.

86
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:45,410
GREETINGS AND FELICITATIONS.

87
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:49,123
HMM. SEND THIS, LIEUTENANT.

88
00:04:49,123 --> 00:04:53,001
<i>USS ENTERPRISE</i> TO SIGNALER
ON PLANET SURFACE.

89
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:55,254
IDENTIFY SELF.

90
00:04:55,254 --> 00:04:58,506
[ BEEPING ]

91
00:04:58,506 --> 00:05:04,304
HIP HIP HOORAH?

92
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:09,059
AND I BELIEVE
IT'S PRONOUNCED TALLYHO.

93
00:05:09,059 --> 00:05:14,106
SOME KIND OF A JOKE, SIR?

94
00:05:14,106 --> 00:05:17,484
I'LL ENTERTAIN ANY THEORIES,
MR. DESALLE, ANY AT ALL.

95
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:18,568
ONE THING IS CERTAIN.

96
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:20,695
OBVIOUSLY, THERE'S LIFE
ON THAT PLANET.

97
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:26,160
YOU'RE QUITE CORRECT, DOCTOR.
PREPARE TRANSPORTER ROOM.

98
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:28,036
REQUEST ASSIGNMENT
TO THE SEARCH PARTY, SIR.

99
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:28,912
NO, MR. SCOTT.

100
00:05:28,912 --> 00:05:31,372
NEITHER YOU NOR I
CAN BE SPARED HERE.

101
00:05:31,372 --> 00:05:33,416
MR. DESALLE, YOU'LL EQUIP
THE LANDING PARTY

102
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:37,045
WITH FULL COMMUNICATIONS,
ARMAMENT AND LIFE SUPPORT GEAR.

103
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:39,256
MR. JAEGER,
YOUR GEOPHYSICAL KNOWLEDGE

104
00:05:39,256 --> 00:05:40,924
MAY BE CRUCIAL DOWN THERE.

105
00:05:40,924 --> 00:05:43,177
DR. McCOY WILL ACCOMPANY.

106
00:05:43,177 --> 00:05:46,387
IF THOSE PECULIAR SIGNALS
ARE COMING FROM CAPTAIN KIRK

107
00:05:46,387 --> 00:05:48,347
OR LIEUTENANT SULU,

108
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:50,684
THEIR RATIONALITY
IS IN QUESTION.

109
00:05:50,684 --> 00:05:52,351
DISMISSED.

110
00:05:52,351 --> 00:05:57,440
[ MUSIC ]

111
00:06:03,362 --> 00:06:05,699
[ BEEPING ]

112
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:07,742
NO MORE MESSAGES FROM BELOW,
SIR,

113
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:09,995
BUT I'VE LOCKED ON
TO THEIR ORIGINAL SOURCE.

114
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:11,121
VERY GOOD.

115
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:14,208
TRANSMIT COORDINATES
TO MR. SCOTT.

116
00:06:14,208 --> 00:06:15,625
ONCE ON THE PLANET'S SURFACE,

117
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,294
YOU'LL ESTABLISH CONTACT WITH US
IMMEDIATELY.

118
00:06:17,294 --> 00:06:21,256
USE THE LASER BEACON
IF NECESSARY.

119
00:06:21,256 --> 00:06:22,381
READY, SCOTT?

120
00:06:22,381 --> 00:06:23,717
READY, MR. SPOCK.

121
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:25,677
ACTIVATE.

122
00:06:25,677 --> 00:06:30,765
[ TRANSPORTER BEAM ]

123
00:06:46,907 --> 00:06:49,076
WHERE ARE YOUR STORMS, JAEGER?

124
00:06:49,076 --> 00:06:54,206
ATMOSPHERE EXACTLY THE SAME
AS OURS.

125
00:07:04,174 --> 00:07:09,596
DESALLE TO<i> ENTERPRISE,</i>
DESALLE TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

126
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:13,308
IT DOESN'T FUNCTION.
WE'RE CUT OFF.

127
00:07:13,308 --> 00:07:15,977
[ BEEPING ]

128
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:17,687
NO RESPONSE.

129
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:19,356
KEEP TRYING WITH YOURS.

130
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:23,277
[ BEEPING ]

131
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:28,365
SOMETHING'S BLOCKING THE BEACON.
GOT TO FIND OPEN GROUND.

132
00:07:38,292 --> 00:07:43,380
JAEGER! McCOY!

133
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:50,971
[ MUSIC ]

134
00:08:47,861 --> 00:08:53,033
IN THE NAME OF HEAVEN,
WHERE ARE WE?

135
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:12,677
LOOK!

136
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:17,765
[ MUSIC ]

137
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:34,199
THERE'S NO READING.
THEY'RE LIKE WAXWORKS FIGURES.

138
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:36,451
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

139
00:09:36,451 --> 00:09:41,540
[ MUSIC ]

140
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:48,880
I MUST SAY THEY MAKE A PERFECTLY
EXQUISITE DISPLAY PAIR,

141
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:54,010
BUT I SUPPOSE
YOU WANT THEM BACK NOW.

142
00:09:57,889 --> 00:10:02,977
WHERE ARE WE?

143
00:10:06,398 --> 00:10:09,650
WELCOME TO AN ISLAND OF PEACE
ON MY STORMY LITTLE PLANET

144
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:11,611
OF GOTHOS.

145
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,405
WHAT HAPPENED?
FILL ME IN.

146
00:10:13,405 --> 00:10:15,782
YOU DISAPPEARED
FROM THE BRIDGE AFTER SULU.

147
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:17,951
WE'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR YOU
FOR FOUR HOURS.

148
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:21,371
YOU MUST EXCUSE MY WHIMSICAL WAY
OF FETCHING YOU HERE.

149
00:10:21,371 --> 00:10:26,543
BUT WHEN I SAW YOU PASSING BY,
I SIMPLY COULD NOT RESIST.

150
00:10:29,504 --> 00:10:33,216
I'M CAPTAIN JAMES KIRK OF
THE UNITED STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

151
00:10:33,216 --> 00:10:36,052
AH, SO YOU ARE THE CAPTAIN
OF THESE BRAVE LADS.

152
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:38,472
MY GREETINGS AND FELICITATIONS,
CAPTAIN.

153
00:10:38,472 --> 00:10:43,184
SO GOOD OF YOU AND YOUR OFFICERS
TO DROP IN.

154
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:45,645
ABSOLUTELY SMASHING.

155
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:47,730
WHO ARE YOU?
WHERE DO YOU COME FROM?

156
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:52,068
GENERAL TRELANE, RETIRED.
AT YOUR SERVICE, SIRS.

157
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:57,865
MY HOME IS YOUR HOME.

158
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:00,285
[ MUSIC ]

159
00:11:00,285 --> 00:11:01,911
WE'VE LOST CONTACT
WITH THE SHIP, CAPTAIN.

160
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:03,121
WE'RE TRAPPED HERE.

161
00:11:03,121 --> 00:11:04,664
I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW DELIGHTED I AM

162
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,333
TO HAVE VISITORS
FROM THE VERY PLANET

163
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:11,379
THAT I'VE MADE MY HOBBY.

164
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:13,298
YES, BUT ACCORDING
TO MY OBSERVATIONS,

165
00:11:13,298 --> 00:11:18,261
I DIDN'T THINK YOU CAPABLE
OF SUCH VOYAGES.

166
00:11:18,261 --> 00:11:22,015
NOTICE THE PERIOD, CAPTAIN,
900 LIGHT YEARS FROM EARTH.

167
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:24,643
IT'S WHAT MIGHT BE SEEN
THROUGH A VIEWING SCOPE

168
00:11:24,643 --> 00:11:26,060
IF IT WERE POWERFUL ENOUGH.

169
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:26,853
AH, YES.

170
00:11:26,853 --> 00:11:28,062
I'VE BEEN LOOKING IN
ON THE DOINGS

171
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:32,691
ON YOUR LIVELY LITTLE EARTH.

172
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:38,239
THEN YOU'VE BEEN LOOKING IN
ON THE DOINGS 900 YEARS PAST.

173
00:11:38,239 --> 00:11:43,662
OH, REALLY?
HAVE I MADE AN ERROR IN TIME?

174
00:11:43,662 --> 00:11:46,080
HOW FALLIBLE OF ME.

175
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,707
OH, I DID SO WANT TO MAKE YOU
FEEL AT HOME.

176
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:50,877
I'M QUITE PROUD OF THE DETAIL.

177
00:11:50,877 --> 00:11:52,045
GENERAL TRELANE...

178
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:55,465
RETIRED, SIR.
JUST SQUIRE TRELANE NOW.

179
00:11:55,465 --> 00:11:59,594
AND YOU MAY CALL ME SQUIRE.
YES, I RATHER FANCY THAT.

180
00:11:59,594 --> 00:12:02,972
FOR WHAT PURPOSE
HAVE YOU IMPRISONED US HERE?

181
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:06,518
IMPRISONED? NONSENSE.
YOU'RE MY GUESTS.

182
00:12:06,518 --> 00:12:09,354
YOU SEE, I JUST FINISHED
MY STUDIES OF YOUR CURIOUS

183
00:12:09,354 --> 00:12:11,105
AND FASCINATING SOCIETY.

184
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:13,858
YOU CAME BY
AT THE MOST PROPITIOUS MOMENT.

185
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:15,569
I WANT TO KNOW
ALL ABOUT YOUR CAMPAIGNS,

186
00:12:15,569 --> 00:12:17,612
YOUR BATTLES,
YOUR MISSIONS OF CONQUEST.

187
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:20,365
OUR MISSIONS ARE PEACEFUL,
NOT TO CONQUEST.

188
00:12:20,365 --> 00:12:21,866
WHEN WE DO BATTLE,

189
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:23,493
IT IS ONLY BECAUSE
WE HAVE NO CHOICE.

190
00:12:23,493 --> 00:12:24,118
[ CHUCKLES ]

191
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:25,412
BUT THAT'S THE OFFICIAL STORY,
EH?

192
00:12:25,412 --> 00:12:27,997
I MUST ASK YOU
TO LET US GO BACK TO OUR SHIP.

193
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:31,334
OH, I WOULDN'T HEAR OF IT.
YOU SHALL JOIN ME IN A REPAST.

194
00:12:31,334 --> 00:12:34,087
I WANT TO LEARN
ALL ABOUT YOUR FEELINGS ON WAR

195
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:36,923
AND KILLING AND CONQUEST,
THAT SORT OF THING.

196
00:12:36,923 --> 00:12:39,926
DO YOU KNOW THAT YOU'RE ONE
OF THE FEW PREDATOR SPECIES

197
00:12:39,926 --> 00:12:45,014
THAT PREYS EVEN ON ITSELF?

198
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,438
NOT YET.

199
00:12:51,438 --> 00:12:54,608
PUT IT ON STUN,
NOT TO KILL, DESALLE.

200
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:56,984
DESALLE, DID YOU SAY?

201
00:12:56,984 --> 00:12:59,195
[ SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE ]

202
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,905
MY ANCESTRY IS FRENCH, YES.

203
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:04,659
AH, MONSIEUR!
[ SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE ]

204
00:13:04,659 --> 00:13:07,537
YOU KNOW, I ADMIRE YOUR NAPOLEON
VERY MUCH.

205
00:13:07,537 --> 00:13:11,916
THIS IS MR. DESALLE,
OUR NAVIGATOR;

206
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:15,754
DR. McCOY, OUR MEDICAL OFFICER;
MR. SULU, OUR HELMSMAN;

207
00:13:15,754 --> 00:13:18,381
AND CARL JAEGER, METEOROLOGIST.

208
00:13:18,381 --> 00:13:22,969
WELCOME, GOOD PHYSICIANER
AND HONORABLE SIR.

209
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:24,721
IS HE KIDDING?

210
00:13:24,721 --> 00:13:27,848
UND, OFFICER JAEGER...

211
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:35,398
[ SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE ]

212
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:38,192
I'M A SCIENTIST,
NOT A MILITARY MAN.

213
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:39,026
OH, COME NOW.

214
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:42,447
WE'RE ALL MILITARY MEN
UNDER THE SKIN.

215
00:13:42,447 --> 00:13:47,494
AND HOW WE DO LOVE OUR UNIFORMS.

216
00:13:51,164 --> 00:13:55,876
WHAT AN INTERESTING WEAPON
YOU'VE GOT THERE.

217
00:13:55,876 --> 00:14:00,881
DO LET ME SEE IT.

218
00:14:04,093 --> 00:14:05,637
YES.

219
00:14:05,637 --> 00:14:07,846
NOW, LET ME SEE.

220
00:14:07,846 --> 00:14:10,141
HOW DOES THIS WORK?

221
00:14:10,141 --> 00:14:11,726
AH, YES.

222
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:16,063
THIS WON'T KILL, AND THIS WILL.

223
00:14:16,063 --> 00:14:19,442
OH.

224
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:21,944
[ PHASER FIRING ]

225
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:24,823
OH, HOW MARVELOUS.

226
00:14:24,823 --> 00:14:26,825
[ PHASER FIRING ]

227
00:14:26,825 --> 00:14:28,493
DEVASTATING.

228
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:33,914
WHY, THIS COULD KILL MILLIONS.

229
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:36,167
WHO WILL YOU START WITH,
MY CREW?

230
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:37,794
ARE WE YOUR NEXT TARGETS?

231
00:14:37,794 --> 00:14:41,214
OH, HOW ABSOLUTELY TYPICAL
OF YOUR SPECIES.

232
00:14:41,214 --> 00:14:44,967
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND SOMETHING,
SO YOU BECOME FEARFUL.

233
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,970
NOW, DO LET ME ANTICIPATE
YOUR NEXT QUESTION.

234
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:50,264
YOU WANT TO KNOW
HOW I MANAGED ALL OF THIS.

235
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,307
THAT'S CORRECT.

236
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:52,266
[ SMIRKS ]

237
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:56,229
WE, MEANING I AND OTHERS, HAVE,
TO STATE THE MATTER BRIEFLY,

238
00:14:56,229 --> 00:14:58,231
PERFECTED A SYSTEM
BY WHICH MATTER

239
00:14:58,231 --> 00:15:01,401
CAN BE TRANSFERRED TO ENERGY
AND BACK TO MATTER AGAIN.

240
00:15:01,401 --> 00:15:03,611
LIKE THE TRANSPORTER SYSTEM
ABOARD THE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

241
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:06,113
OH, A CRUDE EXAMPLE
OF AN INFINITELY

242
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:08,742
MORE SOPHISTICATED PROCESS.

243
00:15:08,742 --> 00:15:12,787
YOU SEE, WE NOT ONLY TRANSPORT
MATTER FROM PLACE TO PLACE,

244
00:15:12,787 --> 00:15:15,874
BUT WE CAN ALTER ITS SHAPE
AT WILL.

245
00:15:15,874 --> 00:15:19,460
THIS DRAWING ROOM,
DID YOU CREATE IT

246
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:21,588
BY REARRANGING MATTER
ON THIS PLANET?

247
00:15:21,588 --> 00:15:23,631
QUITE.

248
00:15:23,631 --> 00:15:25,383
I SEE.

249
00:15:25,383 --> 00:15:26,634
HOW DID YOU MANAGE...

250
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:29,888
DEAR CAPTAIN, YOUR INQUIRIES
ARE BECOMING TIRESOME.

251
00:15:29,888 --> 00:15:32,640
I WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY.
FREE YOURSELF OF CARE.

252
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,350
LET'S ENJOY OURSELVES
IN THE SPIRIT

253
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:36,269
OF MARTIAL GOOD FELLOWSHIP.

254
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:37,478
COME ON, LET'S GO.
WE'RE GETTING OUT OF HERE.

255
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:40,815
TUT, TUT, TUT!
YOU'RE BEING QUITE RUDE.

256
00:15:40,815 --> 00:15:42,609
YOU CAN'T GO.

257
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:45,236
APPARENTLY, YOU NEED
ANOTHER DEMONSTRATION

258
00:15:45,236 --> 00:15:47,947
OF MY AUTHORITY.

259
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:51,785
YES, QUITE.

260
00:15:51,785 --> 00:15:55,747
[ MUSIC ]

261
00:15:55,747 --> 00:16:00,794
[ COUGHING ]

262
00:16:06,591 --> 00:16:09,385
NOW, THAT'S A SAMPLE
OF THE ATMOSPHERE OF THIS PLANET

263
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,930
OUTSIDE MY KINDLY INFLUENCE.

264
00:16:11,930 --> 00:16:16,142
NOW, YOU WILL BEHAVE YOURSELF
HERE, CAPTAIN, WON'T YOU?

265
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:23,232
OR I SHALL BE VERY, VERY ANGRY.

266
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:25,443
[ MUSIC ]

267
00:16:25,443 --> 00:16:28,988
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STARDATE 2125.7.

268
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:31,908
SCIENCE OFFICER SPOCK
REPORTING FOR CAPTAIN KIRK.

269
00:16:31,908 --> 00:16:34,494
WE'VE COMPLETED 14th ORBIT
OF THIS PLANET

270
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:37,664
WITHOUT ESTABLISHING CONTACT
WITH OUR MISSING OFFICERS

271
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,457
OR THE PARTY SENT TO FIND THEM.

272
00:16:39,457 --> 00:16:41,918
SUBSPACE COMMUNICATIONS
REMAIN BLOCKED.

273
00:16:41,918 --> 00:16:44,128
HOWEVER, BY DIVERTING
THE IMPULSE POWER

274
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:46,965
TO OUR SENSORS,
WE HAVE MADE THEM OPERABLE,

275
00:16:46,965 --> 00:16:50,426
AND WE HAVE DETECTED
ONE SMALL AREA ON THE SURFACE

276
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:52,178
WHICH SEEMS RELATIVELY STABLE.

277
00:16:52,178 --> 00:16:54,054
AYE, IT'S THERE, MR. SPOCK.

278
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:56,307
PEACEFUL AS EARTH,
BUT HOW DO YOU EXPLAIN IT?

279
00:16:56,307 --> 00:16:58,893
I DON'T, MR. SCOTT.
IT SIMPLY EXISTS.

280
00:16:58,893 --> 00:17:01,354
ARTIFICIAL PERHAPS
OR A FREAK OF NATURE,

281
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:03,857
BUT THE FACT REMAINS THAT LIFE
CAN EXIST IN THAT AREA.

282
00:17:03,857 --> 00:17:04,983
AYE, IT COULD.

283
00:17:04,983 --> 00:17:07,193
BUT IT COULDN'T MOVE
AROUND MUCH.

284
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:09,153
APPLY A FINE TUNING
ON OUR SENSORS.

285
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:11,656
LOCATE ANY LIFE FORMS
IN THAT STABLE AREA.

286
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:12,740
EVEN IF WE FIND ANY,

287
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:15,201
IT DOESN'T FOLLOW
THAT IT WOULD BE OUR PEOPLE.

288
00:17:15,201 --> 00:17:16,369
AFFIRMATIVE.

289
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:18,496
BUT IF THE CAPTAIN IS DOWN THERE
AND ALIVE,

290
00:17:18,496 --> 00:17:19,998
THAT'S WHERE HE'LL HAVE TO BE.

291
00:17:19,998 --> 00:17:22,625
WE'LL ATTEMPT TO TRANSPORT UP
ANY LIVING BEINGS

292
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:24,084
OUR SENSORS DETECT.

293
00:17:24,084 --> 00:17:25,503
SHOOTING IN THE DARK, MR. SPOCK?

294
00:17:25,503 --> 00:17:29,590
OR STAND BY AND DO NOTHING,
MR. SCOTT.

295
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:33,011
[ MUSIC ]

296
00:17:33,011 --> 00:17:35,513
AND THIS, OF COURSE,
IS AN ARRAY OF YOUR BATTLE FLAGS

297
00:17:35,513 --> 00:17:37,974
AND PENNANTS
DATING BACK TO THE CRUSADES,

298
00:17:37,974 --> 00:17:40,894
TO HANNIBAL'S INVADERS,
THE GRECIAN WAR GALLEYS

299
00:17:40,894 --> 00:17:42,937
AND THE HOARDS OF PERSIA.

300
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:46,900
CAN'T YOU IMAGINE IT, CAPTAIN,
THE THOUSANDS OF MEN

301
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:50,737
MARCHING OFF TO THEIR DEATHS
SINGING BENEATH THESE BANNERS?

302
00:17:50,737 --> 00:17:54,156
DOESN'T IT MAKE YOUR BLOOD
RUN SWIFTLY?

303
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:57,368
CAPTAIN, WHERE COULD HE
POSSIBLY COME FROM?

304
00:17:57,368 --> 00:17:58,118
[ MUSIC ]

305
00:17:58,118 --> 00:18:00,162
WHO IS THIS MANIAC?

306
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:03,374
BETTER SAY, WHAT IS HE?
I MONITORED HIM.

307
00:18:03,374 --> 00:18:05,877
WHAT I FOUND WAS UNBELIEVABLE.

308
00:18:05,877 --> 00:18:07,336
NOT ALIVE?

309
00:18:07,336 --> 00:18:11,758
NOT IN THE WAY WE DEFINE LIFE.
NO TRACE, ZERO.

310
00:18:11,758 --> 00:18:14,677
YOU MEAN, IT SHOWS HE'S DEAD?

311
00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:17,597
IT DOESN'T EVEN SHOW
THAT HE EXISTS AT ALL,

312
00:18:17,597 --> 00:18:19,599
ALIVE OR DEAD.

313
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:22,142
NOTICE THE WOOD FIRE, CAPTAIN,
BURNING STEADILY,

314
00:18:22,142 --> 00:18:23,352
EMBER BED GLOWING?

315
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:28,107
IT DOESN'T GIVE OFF
ANY HEAT AT ALL.

316
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:30,234
FIRE WITHOUT HEAT,

317
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:32,528
MISTAKING ALL THIS
FOR PRESENT-DAY EARTH

318
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:36,449
WITHOUT TAKING INTO ACCOUNT
THE TIME DIFFERENTIAL.

319
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:38,701
WHATEVER WE'RE DEALING WITH,

320
00:18:38,701 --> 00:18:41,746
HE CERTAINLY
ISN'T ALL KNOWLEDGEABLE.

321
00:18:41,746 --> 00:18:45,165
HE MAKES MISTAKES.

322
00:18:45,165 --> 00:18:48,086
DISCUSSING DEEP-LAID PLANS,
I'LL WAGER.

323
00:18:48,086 --> 00:18:49,169
[ CHUCKLES ]

324
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:52,840
I CANNOT WAIT
TO SEE THEM EVOLVE.

325
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,468
TRELANE, WE HAVEN'T PLANNED--

326
00:18:55,468 --> 00:18:56,761
TUT, TUT.

327
00:18:56,761 --> 00:19:00,139
DO NOT THINK THAT I DEPLORE
YOUR MARTIAL VIRTUE OF DECEPTION

328
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:01,307
AND STRATAGEM.

329
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:02,600
QUITE THE CONTRARY.

330
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,603
I HAVE NOTHING BUT ADMIRATION
FOR YOUR WHOLE SPECIES.

331
00:19:05,603 --> 00:19:07,480
IF YOUR ADMIRATION IS GENUINE,

332
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,774
YOU MUST HAVE RESPECT
FOR OUR SENSE OF DUTY TOO.

333
00:19:09,774 --> 00:19:12,110
OUR SHIP HAS NEED OF US.
WE HAVE TASKS TO PERFORM.

334
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:15,071
OH, I CAN'T LET YOU GO NOW.

335
00:19:15,071 --> 00:19:18,074
I WAS GETTING A BIT BORED
UNTIL YOU CAME.

336
00:19:18,074 --> 00:19:20,785
YOU MUST STAY.

337
00:19:20,785 --> 00:19:22,244
I INSIST.

338
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:23,162
FOR HOW LONG?

339
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:24,497
UNTIL THIS IS OVER, OF COURSE.

340
00:19:24,497 --> 00:19:25,372
UNTIL WHAT IS OVER?

341
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:27,583
DEAR CAPTAIN, SO MANY QUESTIONS.

342
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:29,669
MAKE THE MOST
OF AN UNCERTAIN FUTURE.

343
00:19:29,669 --> 00:19:34,548
ENJOY YOURSELVES TODAY.
TOMORROW MAY NEVER COME AT ALL.

344
00:19:34,548 --> 00:19:36,092
TRELANE, EVEN IF WE WANTED
TO STAY,

345
00:19:36,092 --> 00:19:37,510
OUR COMPANIONS ARE MISSING US.

346
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:38,511
YES.

347
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:41,221
I MUST EXPERIENCE
YOUR SENSE OF CONCERN,

348
00:19:41,221 --> 00:19:42,598
YOUR GRIEF AT THE SEPARATION.

349
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:46,019
THERE ARE 400 MEN AND WOMEN
ABOARD THAT SHIP.

350
00:19:46,019 --> 00:19:47,603
WOMEN?

351
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:52,025
DO YOU MEAN THAT YOU ACTUALLY
HAVE MEMBERS OF THE FAIRER SEX

352
00:19:52,025 --> 00:19:53,860
AMONG YOUR CREW?

353
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:56,946
OH, HOW CHARMING.

354
00:19:56,946 --> 00:19:59,615
AND THEY MUST BE
ALL VERY BEAUTIFUL.

355
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:02,535
AND I SHALL BE SO VERY GALLANT
TO THEM.

356
00:20:02,535 --> 00:20:05,788
HERE, LET ME FETCH THEM DOWN
AT ONCE.

357
00:20:05,788 --> 00:20:07,581
NO.

358
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:08,875
NO?

359
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:10,376
THIS GAME HAS GONE ON
LONG ENOUGH.

360
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:11,961
THOSE ARE CRUCIAL
OPERATING PERSONNEL.

361
00:20:11,961 --> 00:20:12,712
YOU CAN'T--

362
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:14,630
I CAN DO ANYTHING I WANT.

363
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:17,383
I SHOULD THINK THAT YOU
WOULD HAVE REALIZED THAT BY NOW.

364
00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:18,592
[ BEEPING ]

365
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:21,012
CAPTAIN, RECEIVING
A TRANSPORTER SIGNAL.

366
00:20:21,012 --> 00:20:23,890
TRANSPORTER SIGNAL?
WHAT DOES HE MEAN?

367
00:20:23,890 --> 00:20:25,099
YOU MUST TELL ME.

368
00:20:25,099 --> 00:20:28,936
IT MEANS, TRELANE,
THE PARTY'S OVER,

369
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:29,979
THANKS TO MR. SPOCK.

370
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:34,192
WAIT! I WON'T HAVE THIS!
I HAVEN'T DISMISSED YOU YET!

371
00:20:34,192 --> 00:20:37,778
STOP! I WON'T HAVE THIS!

372
00:20:41,991 --> 00:20:44,827
EVERYONE'S STATIONED.
REPORT, MR. SPOCK.

373
00:20:44,827 --> 00:20:46,370
HOW WERE OUR SCANNERS
ABLE TO PENETRATE

374
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:47,454
THAT RADIATION FIELD?

375
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:49,207
THEY DIDN'T, CAPTAIN,
NOT CLEARLY.

376
00:20:49,207 --> 00:20:51,625
WE MERELY BEAMED UP
ALL LIFE FORMS IN A GIVEN AREA.

377
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,044
WHICH MEANS TRELANE
IS NOT A LIFE FORM

378
00:20:53,044 --> 00:20:55,004
AS WE KNOW IT
OR HE'D BE BEAMING THROUGH NOW.

379
00:20:55,004 --> 00:20:57,381
PREPARE TO WARP OUT OF HERE
AT ONCE, MAXIMUM SPEED.

380
00:20:57,381 --> 00:21:01,177
[ MUSIC ]

381
00:21:08,308 --> 00:21:09,393
CAPTAIN, I WAS SO WORRIED.

382
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:11,979
SCOTTY, WE'RE GONNA NEED
EVERY OUNCE OF YOUR ENGINES.

383
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:13,439
WE'RE GONNA PUT
A HUNDRED MILLION MILES

384
00:21:13,439 --> 00:21:14,607
BETWEEN US AND THAT MAD MAN.

385
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:16,025
AYE, AYE, SIR.

386
00:21:16,025 --> 00:21:16,817
I'M QUAKING, BUT I DON'T KNOW

387
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,861
WHETHER IT'S WITH LAUGHTER
OR TERROR.

388
00:21:18,861 --> 00:21:21,906
DOCTOR, WHAT WAS IT?
WHAT WAS DOWN THERE?

389
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:25,993
WELL, IT WAS A--OH, FORGET IT.

390
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:27,620
LOOK!

391
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:32,332
[ MUSIC ]

392
00:21:32,332 --> 00:21:34,710
WHERE ARE ALL YOUR WEAPONS,
CAPTAIN?

393
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:37,880
DON'T YOU DISPLAY YOUR WEAPONS?

394
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,006
TRELANE.

395
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:43,052
DON'T FRET, CAPTAIN.
I'M ONLY A BIT UPSET WITH YOU.

396
00:21:43,052 --> 00:21:45,805
BUT THIS MR. SPOCK
YOU MENTIONED,

397
00:21:45,805 --> 00:21:48,515
THE ONE RESPONSIBLE
FOR THAT UNSEEMLY IMPUDENT ACT

398
00:21:48,515 --> 00:21:51,894
OF TAKING YOU FROM ME,
WHICH IS HE?

399
00:21:51,894 --> 00:21:53,854
I AM SPOCK.

400
00:21:53,854 --> 00:21:58,818
SURELY NOT AN OFFICER.
HE ISN'T QUITE HUMAN, IS HE?

401
00:21:58,818 --> 00:22:01,487
MY FATHER
IS FROM THE PLANET VULCAN.

402
00:22:01,487 --> 00:22:03,322
AND ARE ITS NATIVES PREDATORY?

403
00:22:03,322 --> 00:22:07,534
NOT GENERALLY,
BUT THERE HAVE BEEN EXCEPTIONS.

404
00:22:07,534 --> 00:22:11,831
REALLY?
YOU WILL SEE TO HIS PUNISHMENT?

405
00:22:11,831 --> 00:22:13,791
ON THE CONTRARY,
I COMMEND HIS ACTION.

406
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:17,419
BUT I DON'T LIKE HIM.

407
00:22:19,088 --> 00:22:20,089
GET OFF MY SHIP.

408
00:22:20,089 --> 00:22:22,591
OH, ROT!
YOU'RE ALL GOING BACK WITH ME.

409
00:22:22,591 --> 00:22:23,676
WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

410
00:22:23,676 --> 00:22:24,718
NONSENSE.

411
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:26,804
I HAVE AN ABSOLUTELY
ENCHANTING SOJOURN

412
00:22:26,804 --> 00:22:31,225
ON GOTHOS PLANET FOR ALL OF YOU,
AND YOU SHAN'T SPOIL IT FOR ME.

413
00:22:31,225 --> 00:22:33,311
ANYWAY, THE DECOR
OF MY DRAWING ROOM

414
00:22:33,311 --> 00:22:36,939
IS MUCH MORE APPROPRIATE
AND TASTEFUL.

415
00:22:36,939 --> 00:22:38,899
DON'T YOU AGREE?

416
00:22:38,899 --> 00:22:40,109
NO.

417
00:22:40,109 --> 00:22:44,071
BUT SO MUCH MORE FITTING,
HONORABLE SIR.

418
00:22:44,071 --> 00:22:47,908
YOU...

419
00:22:47,908 --> 00:22:51,495
OH, WHAT PRIMITIVE FURY.

420
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:53,873
WHY, HE'S THE VERY SOUL
OF SUBLIME SAVAGERY.

421
00:22:53,873 --> 00:22:57,126
TRELANE, LET HIM GO.

422
00:22:57,126 --> 00:22:59,753
WE HAVEN'T EVEN GOT OUR PHASERS.

423
00:22:59,753 --> 00:23:00,671
YES, OF COURSE.

424
00:23:00,671 --> 00:23:03,007
I FORGET THAT I SHOULDN'T
FRIGHTEN YOU TOO MUCH.

425
00:23:03,007 --> 00:23:06,802
BUT I WARN YOU.
YOU CAN'T PROVOKE ME AGAIN.

426
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:10,388
COME, EVERYONE.
LET'S FORGET YOUR BAD MANNERS.

427
00:23:10,388 --> 00:23:13,684
LET'S BE FULL OF MERRY TALK
AND SALLIES OF WIT.

428
00:23:13,684 --> 00:23:15,853
WE HAVE VICTUALS
TO DELIGHT THE PALATE

429
00:23:15,853 --> 00:23:19,982
AND BRAVE COMPANY
TO DELIGHT THE MIND.

430
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:25,029
COME, DOCTOR, DO PARTAKE.

431
00:23:27,823 --> 00:23:33,162
AH, YOU'VE BEEN QUITE DERELICT
IN YOUR SOCIAL DUTIES, CAPTAIN.

432
00:23:33,162 --> 00:23:36,456
YOU HAVEN'T INTRODUCED ME
TO THE CHARMING CONTINGENT

433
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:38,376
OF YOUR CREW.

434
00:23:38,376 --> 00:23:40,878
THIS IS GENERAL TRELANE.

435
00:23:40,878 --> 00:23:42,380
RETIRED.

436
00:23:42,380 --> 00:23:44,340
BUT IF YOU PREFER,
YOU MAY ADDRESS ME

437
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:47,551
AS THE LONELY SQUIRE OF GOTHOS,
DEAR LADIES.

438
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:49,303
LIEUTENANT UHURA
OF COMMUNICATIONS.

439
00:23:49,303 --> 00:23:52,639
AH, A NUBIAN PRIZE.

440
00:23:55,601 --> 00:23:58,520
TAKEN ON ONE OF YOUR RAIDS
OF CONQUEST, NO DOUBT, CAPTAIN?

441
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,064
NO DOUBT.

442
00:24:00,064 --> 00:24:03,025
SHE HAS THE MELTING EYES
OF THE QUEEN OF SHEBA,

443
00:24:03,025 --> 00:24:05,903
THE SAME LOVELY COLORING.

444
00:24:05,903 --> 00:24:07,654
AND THIS.

445
00:24:07,654 --> 00:24:10,574
IS THIS THE FACE
THAT LAUNCHED A THOUSAND SHIPS

446
00:24:10,574 --> 00:24:13,286
AND BURNT THE TOPLESS TOWERS
OF ILIUM?

447
00:24:13,286 --> 00:24:16,247
FAIR HELEN,
MAKE ME A MORTAL WITH A KISS.

448
00:24:16,247 --> 00:24:18,456
YEOMAN TERESA ROSS.

449
00:24:18,456 --> 00:24:23,045
I BELIEVE YOU HAVE MET
OUR SCIENCE OFFICER, MR. SPOCK.

450
00:24:23,045 --> 00:24:26,299
YOU DO REALIZE, DON'T YOU,
THAT IT'S IN DEFERENCE

451
00:24:26,299 --> 00:24:28,384
TO THE CAPTAIN
THAT I BROUGHT YOU HERE?

452
00:24:28,384 --> 00:24:30,136
AFFIRMATIVE.

453
00:24:30,136 --> 00:24:32,679
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
IF I LIKE YOUR TONE.

454
00:24:32,679 --> 00:24:33,973
IT'S MOST CHALLENGING.

455
00:24:33,973 --> 00:24:36,558
IS THAT WHAT YOU'RE DOING,
CHALLENGING ME?

456
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,144
I OBJECT TO YOU.

457
00:24:38,144 --> 00:24:40,771
I OBJECT TO INTELLECT
WITHOUT DISCIPLINE.

458
00:24:40,771 --> 00:24:44,066
I OBJECT TO POWER
WITHOUT CONSTRUCTIVE PURPOSE.

459
00:24:44,066 --> 00:24:48,612
OH, MR. SPOCK, YOU DO HAVE
ONE SAVING GRACE AFTER ALL.

460
00:24:48,612 --> 00:24:54,076
YOU'RE ILL-MANNERED.
THE HUMAN HALF OF YOU, NO DOUBT.

461
00:24:56,494 --> 00:25:01,125
AH, COME, MY LITTLE WOOD NYMPH.
WON'T YOU DANCE WITH YOUR SWAY?

462
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:04,628
GIVE US SOME SPRIGHTLY MUSIC,
MY DEAR GIRL.

463
00:25:04,628 --> 00:25:06,588
OH, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO PLAY THIS.

464
00:25:06,588 --> 00:25:09,633
OF COURSE, YOU DO.

465
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:13,346
[ MUSIC ]

466
00:25:40,914 --> 00:25:45,627
CAPTAIN, HOW FAR DO WE GO ALONG
WITH THIS CHARADE?

467
00:25:45,627 --> 00:25:47,629
UNTIL WE CAN THINK OUR WAY OUT.

468
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:51,633
MEANWHILE, WE ACCEPT
THIS HOSPITALITY.

469
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:53,386
WELL, YOU SHOULD TASTE
THIS FOOD.

470
00:25:53,386 --> 00:25:55,679
SCRAW WOULD TASTE BETTER
THAN HIS MEAT

471
00:25:55,679 --> 00:25:57,931
AND WATER 100 TIMES BETTER
THAN HIS BRANDY.

472
00:25:57,931 --> 00:25:59,933
NOTHING HAS ANY TASTE AT ALL.

473
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:03,479
IT MAY BE UNAPPETIZING, DOCTOR,
BUT IT IS VERY LOGICAL.

474
00:26:03,479 --> 00:26:06,440
THERE'S THAT MAGIC WORD AGAIN.

475
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:09,567
DOES YOUR LOGIC FIND THIS
FASCINATING, MR. SPOCK?

476
00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:13,364
FASCINATING IS A WORD I USE
FOR THE UNEXPECTED.

477
00:26:13,364 --> 00:26:16,992
IN THIS CASE, I SHOULD THINK
INTERESTING WOULD SUFFICE.

478
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:19,953
YOU DON'T FIND THIS UNEXPECTED,
MR. SPOCK?

479
00:26:19,953 --> 00:26:22,998
THAT HIS FOOD HAS NO TASTE,
HIS WINE NO FLAVOR?

480
00:26:22,998 --> 00:26:24,166
NO.

481
00:26:24,166 --> 00:26:27,294
IT SIMPLY MEANS THAT TRELANE
KNOWS ALL OF THE EARTH FORMS,

482
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:29,213
BUT NONE OF THE SUBSTANCE.

483
00:26:29,213 --> 00:26:30,630
AND THAT HE'S FALLIBLE.

484
00:26:30,630 --> 00:26:33,259
HE CAN'T BE ALL POWERFUL,

485
00:26:33,259 --> 00:26:35,928
WHICH MEANS HE HAS SOMETHING
HELPING HIM.

486
00:26:35,928 --> 00:26:37,346
EVIDENTLY.

487
00:26:37,346 --> 00:26:41,517
A MACHINE? A DEVICE?

488
00:26:41,517 --> 00:26:46,397
SOMETHING WHICH DOES
THESE THINGS FOR HIM.

489
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:56,115
AH, MY DEAR,
DON'T WE MAKE A GRACEFUL PAIR?

490
00:26:56,115 --> 00:26:58,451
EXCEPT FOR ONE SMALL DETAIL.

491
00:26:58,451 --> 00:27:04,123
THAT DRESS HARDLY MATCHES
THIS CHARMING SCENE.

492
00:27:07,709 --> 00:27:10,504
AH, YES, THAT'S MORE
OF WHAT WE WANT.

493
00:27:10,504 --> 00:27:15,008
THE DASHING WARRIOR
AND HIS ELEGANT MAIDEN.

494
00:27:30,190 --> 00:27:34,403
THAT MIRROR,
PART OF HIS AUDIENCE, HIS EGO.

495
00:27:34,403 --> 00:27:36,280
HE NEVER WANDERS FROM IT.

496
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:40,033
IS IT EGO OR SOMETHING ELSE?

497
00:27:40,033 --> 00:27:41,076
EXPLAIN.

498
00:27:41,076 --> 00:27:42,244
THE MIRROR.

499
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:43,162
WHAT ABOUT IT?

500
00:27:43,162 --> 00:27:46,248
YOU NOTED YOURSELF HE NEVER
GETS VERY FAR AWAY FROM IT.

501
00:27:46,248 --> 00:27:47,416
I SUPPOSE IT COULD BE VANITY.

502
00:27:47,416 --> 00:27:50,961
NO, NO, MR. SPOCK.
THAT'S NOT THE REASON.

503
00:27:53,172 --> 00:27:56,800
WHAT KIND OF A MACHINE
COULD DO THESE THINGS?

504
00:27:56,800 --> 00:28:01,763
A MACHINE WITH THE ABILITY
TO TURN ENERGY INTO MATTER

505
00:28:01,763 --> 00:28:03,932
GUIDED BY THOUGHT WAVES.

506
00:28:03,932 --> 00:28:06,810
IT WOULD HAVE
A VERY COMPLEX MEMORY BANK

507
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:08,770
AND BE EXTREMELY SOPHISTICATED.

508
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:11,440
LIKE A COMPUTER, ONLY MUCH MORE.

509
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,733
COULD THE MACHINE
THAT MAINTAINS THE ENVIRONMENT

510
00:28:13,733 --> 00:28:17,488
IN THIS IMMEDIATE AREA
BE KEPT IN THIS HOUSE?

511
00:28:17,488 --> 00:28:19,031
I THINK NOT.

512
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:23,035
A DEVICE CAPABLE OF KEEPING OUT
THIS PLANET'S NATURAL ATMOSPHERE

513
00:28:23,035 --> 00:28:24,453
WOULD BE IMMENSE.

514
00:28:24,453 --> 00:28:28,541
GOOD. I AGREE.
THAT LEAVES ME FREE.

515
00:28:28,541 --> 00:28:30,167
FREE, CAPTAIN?

516
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:34,087
IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN, MR. SPOCK,

517
00:28:34,087 --> 00:28:41,845
I THINK I CAN TURN
HIS LIGHTS OFF AT THE SOURCE.

518
00:28:44,682 --> 00:28:47,267
DON'T BE TOO UPSET
BY WHAT YOU SEE, GENTLEMEN.

519
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:48,310
AFTER ALL, HIS ACTIONS

520
00:28:48,310 --> 00:28:52,523
ARE THOSE OF AN IMMATURE,
UNBALANCED MIND.

521
00:28:52,523 --> 00:28:54,608
I OVERHEARD THAT REMARK,
CAPTAIN.

522
00:28:54,608 --> 00:28:56,276
I'M AFRAID
I'LL HAVE TO DISPENSE WITH YOU.

523
00:28:56,276 --> 00:28:58,195
YOU ONLY HEARD PART OF IT.
I JUST STARTED.

524
00:28:58,195 --> 00:28:59,071
OH?

525
00:28:59,071 --> 00:28:59,697
YES.

526
00:28:59,697 --> 00:29:01,281
I WANT YOU
TO LEAVE MY CREWMEN ALONE.

527
00:29:01,281 --> 00:29:03,116
I WANT YOU TO LEAVE
MY CREW WOMEN ALONE TOO.

528
00:29:03,116 --> 00:29:04,451
YOU'RE NOT TO DANCE WITH HIM.
I DON'T LIKE IT.

529
00:29:04,451 --> 00:29:05,994
DOES IT ACTUALLY MAKE YOU ANGRY,
CAPTAIN?

530
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:07,413
I DON'T WANT YOU
ACCEPTING HIS GIFTS EITHER.

531
00:29:07,413 --> 00:29:08,247
CAPTAIN, PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.

532
00:29:08,247 --> 00:29:10,165
WELL, I DO BELIEVE
THAT THE DEAR CAPTAIN

533
00:29:10,165 --> 00:29:10,790
IS JEALOUS OF ME.

534
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:12,834
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU BELIEVE.
JUST KEEP YOUR HANDS OFF HER.

535
00:29:12,834 --> 00:29:15,713
OH, HOW CURIOUSLY HUMAN.
HOW WONDERFULLY BARBARIC.

536
00:29:15,713 --> 00:29:17,130
I'VE HAD ENOUGH
OF YOUR INSULTING ATTENTIONS

537
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:18,006
TO HER.

538
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:19,299
OF COURSE, YOU HAVE.

539
00:29:19,299 --> 00:29:20,842
AFTER ALL,
THAT'S THE ROOT OF THE MATTER,

540
00:29:20,842 --> 00:29:21,760
ISN'T IT?

541
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:23,470
YOU FIGHT FOR THE ATTENTION,
THE ADMIRATION,

542
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:24,763
THE POSSESSION OF WOMEN.

543
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:28,684
IF IT'S FIGHTING THAT YOU WANT,
YOU MAY HAVE IT.

544
00:29:28,684 --> 00:29:30,936
ARE YOU CHALLENGING ME
TO A DUEL?

545
00:29:30,936 --> 00:29:32,438
IF YOU HAVE THE COURAGE.

546
00:29:32,438 --> 00:29:34,856
OH, THIS IS BETTER
THAN I'D PLANNED.

547
00:29:34,856 --> 00:29:38,694
I SHALL NOT SHIRK
AN AFFAIR OF HONOR.

548
00:29:44,450 --> 00:29:46,326
A MATCHED SET JUST LIKE THE PAIR

549
00:29:46,326 --> 00:29:52,207
THAT SLEW
YOUR HEROIC ALEXANDER HAMILTON.

550
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:57,296
AND, CAPTAIN, I NEVER MISS.

551
00:30:06,888 --> 00:30:11,268
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STARDATE 2126.1,
DELAYED REPORT.

552
00:30:11,268 --> 00:30:13,228
THE WHOLE BRIDGE CREW
ARE THE UNWILLING GUESTS

553
00:30:13,228 --> 00:30:16,315
OF THE CREATURE
WHO CALLS HIMSELF TRELANE.

554
00:30:16,315 --> 00:30:19,610
WE ARE WEAPONLESS, POWERLESS,
AND OUR ONLY HOPE OF ESCAPE

555
00:30:19,610 --> 00:30:23,905
WITH THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
LIES IN PLAYING HIS GAMES.

556
00:30:23,905 --> 00:30:27,993
I'VE DECIDED TO MAKE MY MOVE
WITH THE FIELD OF HONOR GAME

557
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:30,370
AND EVERYTHING DEPENDS
ON MY ONE CHANCE

558
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:33,290
WITH THE ANCIENT DUELING PISTOL.

559
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,750
OH, HOW FASCINATING.

560
00:30:34,750 --> 00:30:37,795
I'M PARTY
TO AN ACTUAL HUMAN DUEL.

561
00:30:37,795 --> 00:30:38,629
ARE YOU READY?

562
00:30:38,629 --> 00:30:39,838
QUITE READY, SIR.

563
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:41,632
WE SHALL TEST
EACH OTHER'S COURAGE,

564
00:30:41,632 --> 00:30:43,592
AND THEN?

565
00:30:43,592 --> 00:30:46,094
AND THEN WE SHALL SEE.

566
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:47,887
ENOUGH TALK.
LET'S GET ON WITH IT.

567
00:30:47,887 --> 00:30:52,934
AS YOU WILL, SIR.
HONOR WILL BE SERVED, EH?

568
00:30:52,934 --> 00:30:53,935
OH, WAIT!

569
00:30:53,935 --> 00:30:57,981
AS THE ONE CHALLENGED,
I CLAIM THE FIRST SHOT.

570
00:30:57,981 --> 00:30:59,483
WE SHOOT TOGETHER.

571
00:30:59,483 --> 00:31:02,444
IT'S MY GAME AND MY RULES.

572
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:05,113
BUT IF YOU NEED
TO BE PERSUADED...

573
00:31:05,113 --> 00:31:10,494
[ MUSIC ]

574
00:31:13,455 --> 00:31:14,748
ALL RIGHT.

575
00:31:14,748 --> 00:31:18,877
CAPTAIN?

576
00:31:34,434 --> 00:31:37,979
[ GUNSHOT ]

577
00:31:37,979 --> 00:31:42,442
AND NOW, CAPTAIN,
HOW DO YOU HAVE THE EXPRESSION?

578
00:31:42,442 --> 00:31:47,072
MY FATE IS IN YOUR HANDS.

579
00:32:00,293 --> 00:32:05,257
[ GUNSHOT ]

580
00:32:10,888 --> 00:32:14,266
YOU'VE RUINED EVERYTHING!

581
00:32:14,266 --> 00:32:17,018
THE MACHINE.

582
00:32:17,018 --> 00:32:19,396
CAPTAIN, SUBSPACE INTERFERENCE
IS CLEARING.

583
00:32:19,396 --> 00:32:20,856
TRY TO CONTACT THE SHIP.

584
00:32:20,856 --> 00:32:23,650
OH, THE REMARKABLE TREACHERY
OF THIS SPECIES.

585
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:25,985
GO ON, TRELANE, LOOK AT IT.
IT'S OVER.

586
00:32:25,985 --> 00:32:28,614
YOUR POWER IS BLANKED OUT.
YOU'RE FINISHED.

587
00:32:28,614 --> 00:32:32,158
YOU'VE EARNED MY WRATH.
GO BACK.

588
00:32:32,158 --> 00:32:35,995
GO BACK TO YOUR SHIP,
ALL OF YOU, AND PREPARE.

589
00:32:35,995 --> 00:32:41,835
YOU'RE ALL DEAD MEN,
YOU ESPECIALLY, CAPTAIN.

590
00:32:45,338 --> 00:32:49,384
TRELANE.

591
00:32:49,384 --> 00:32:51,303
EVERYONE, WE'RE GETTING OUT
OF HERE NOW.

592
00:32:51,303 --> 00:32:52,095
[ BEEPING ]

593
00:32:52,095 --> 00:32:54,306
THIS IS THE CAPTAIN.
COMMENCE BEAMING UP.

594
00:32:54,306 --> 00:32:55,766
MAXIMUM SPEED.

595
00:32:55,766 --> 00:33:01,438
[ MUSIC ]

596
00:33:01,438 --> 00:33:04,190
SET COURSE FOR COLONY BETA SIX.

597
00:33:04,190 --> 00:33:06,526
LAID IN, SIR.

598
00:33:06,526 --> 00:33:08,987
FULL POWER ACCELERATION
FROM ORBIT, MR. SCOTT.

599
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:10,029
Full power, sir.

600
00:33:10,029 --> 00:33:13,158
EMERGENCY WARP AT THE EARLIEST
POSSIBLE MOMENT, MR. SULU.

601
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:17,203
STANDING BY TO WARP SPEED.

602
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:23,543
SHALL I MAKE A FULL REPORT
TO SPACEFLEET COMMAND, SIR?

603
00:33:23,543 --> 00:33:26,296
NOT YET.
THEY MAY TRACE OUR BEAM.

604
00:33:26,296 --> 00:33:30,300
WAIT UNTIL WE'RE WELL OUT
OF RANGE.

605
00:33:30,300 --> 00:33:32,218
CAN WE KNOW WHAT HIS RANGE IS,
CAPTAIN?

606
00:33:32,218 --> 00:33:34,847
WE CAN TAKE AN EDUCATED GUESS
AT THE POINT WE FIRST ENTERED

607
00:33:34,847 --> 00:33:36,515
THEIR SOLAR SYSTEM.

608
00:33:36,515 --> 00:33:39,685
STILL NO SIGN OF PURSUIT.
INSTRUMENTS CLEAR, SIR.

609
00:33:39,685 --> 00:33:44,481
GOOD.

610
00:33:47,734 --> 00:33:49,862
MAY I TAKE A MOMENT TO CHANGE?

611
00:33:49,862 --> 00:33:52,489
YES, I THINK YOU MIGHT.

612
00:33:52,489 --> 00:33:54,950
TURN IN YOUR GLASS SLIPPERS.
THE BALL IS OVER.

613
00:33:54,950 --> 00:33:58,996
GLADLY, CAPTAIN.

614
00:34:03,709 --> 00:34:07,337
HARD TO BELIEVE
THAT IT NEVER HAPPENED.

615
00:34:07,337 --> 00:34:09,339
CAPTAIN, WE'RE ABOUT TO WARP.

616
00:34:09,339 --> 00:34:10,757
LIGHT BODY AHEAD.

617
00:34:10,757 --> 00:34:16,179
[ MUSIC ]

618
00:34:17,931 --> 00:34:19,599
COLLISION COURSE.

619
00:34:19,599 --> 00:34:23,854
HARD TO PORT, MR. SULU.

620
00:34:29,609 --> 00:34:33,112
THAT WAS THE PLANET GOTHOS,
CAPTAIN.

621
00:34:33,112 --> 00:34:35,407
GOTHOS.

622
00:34:35,407 --> 00:34:37,409
MR. SULU,
HAVE WE BEEN GOING IN CIRCLES?

623
00:34:37,409 --> 00:34:39,745
NO, SIR.
ALL INSTRUMENTS SHOW ON COURSE.

624
00:34:39,745 --> 00:34:44,123
GOTHOS AGAIN, CAPTAIN.

625
00:34:44,123 --> 00:34:48,795
HARD OVER, MR. SULU.

626
00:34:51,924 --> 00:34:53,425
CAT AND MOUSE GAME.

627
00:34:53,425 --> 00:34:54,634
WITH US AS THE MOUSE.

628
00:34:54,634 --> 00:34:55,969
THERE IT IS AGAIN, DEAD AHEAD.

629
00:34:55,969 --> 00:34:58,013
90 DEGREES TO STARBOARD,
MR. SULU.

630
00:34:58,013 --> 00:35:01,767
TURNING, CAPTAIN.

631
00:35:01,767 --> 00:35:04,811
NOT VEERING OFF FROM IT.

632
00:35:04,811 --> 00:35:09,900
90 DEGREES SOUTHPORT, MR. SULU.
ADJUST.

633
00:35:11,568 --> 00:35:14,153
TURN COMPLETED
AND STILL ACCELERATING

634
00:35:14,153 --> 00:35:15,530
TOWARD THE PLANET.

635
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:21,286
OR IT TOWARD US.

636
00:35:21,286 --> 00:35:23,121
DECELERATE INTO ORBIT.
PREPARE TRANSPORTER ROOM.

637
00:35:23,121 --> 00:35:25,290
CAPTAIN,
YOU'RE NOT BEAMING DOWN.

638
00:35:25,290 --> 00:35:26,750
YES, I AM, DR. McCOY.

639
00:35:26,750 --> 00:35:29,461
I AM GOING TO SEE
OUR PLAYFUL MR. TRELANE

640
00:35:29,461 --> 00:35:33,339
AND WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO MAKE HIM GIVE UP OUR SHIP.

641
00:35:33,339 --> 00:35:34,340
STAND BY, COMMUNICATIONS.

642
00:35:34,340 --> 00:35:36,217
MR. SPOCK, IF YOU DON'T RECEIVE
A MESSAGE FROM ME

643
00:35:36,217 --> 00:35:38,720
WITHIN THE HOUR,
LEAVE THE VICINITY AT ONCE.

644
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:43,934
NO TURNING BACK.

645
00:35:46,103 --> 00:35:51,441
THE PRISONER MAY APPROACH
THE BENCH.

646
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:57,948
TRELANE.

647
00:36:02,201 --> 00:36:04,913
ANY ATTEMPT TO DEMONSTRATIONS
WILL WEIGH AGAINST YOU

648
00:36:04,913 --> 00:36:06,372
WITH THE COURT.

649
00:36:06,372 --> 00:36:07,165
AND THIS TIME,

650
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:11,920
MY INSTRUMENTALITY
IS UNBREAKABLE.

651
00:36:13,713 --> 00:36:15,381
I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF YOUR GAMES.

652
00:36:15,381 --> 00:36:20,512
OH, THE ABSURDITY
OF THESE INFERIOR BEINGS.

653
00:36:22,221 --> 00:36:24,975
AND NOW, CAPTAIN JAMES KIRK,
YOU STAND ACCUSED

654
00:36:24,975 --> 00:36:29,479
OF THE HIGH CRIME OF TREASON
AGAINST A SUPERIOR AUTHORITY,

655
00:36:29,479 --> 00:36:35,401
CONSPIRACY AND THE ATTEMPT
TO FOMENT INSURRECTION.

656
00:36:35,401 --> 00:36:36,903
HOW DO YOU PLEAD?

657
00:36:36,903 --> 00:36:39,656
I HAVEN'T COME TO PLEAD
IN YOUR COURT, TRELANE.

658
00:36:39,656 --> 00:36:41,533
I WARN YOU,
ANYTHING YOU MIGHT SAY

659
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:44,410
HAS ALREADY BEEN TAKEN DOWN
IN EVIDENCE AGAINST YOU.

660
00:36:44,410 --> 00:36:47,413
I'VE COME FOR ONE PURPOSE,
TO GET BACK MY SHIP.

661
00:36:47,413 --> 00:36:48,414
IRRELEVANT.

662
00:36:48,414 --> 00:36:50,917
WE'VE MADE YOU ANGRY
WITH OUR WILL TO SURVIVE,

663
00:36:50,917 --> 00:36:51,835
HAVE WE?

664
00:36:51,835 --> 00:36:53,045
UNCALLED FOR.

665
00:36:53,045 --> 00:36:55,172
THEN VENT YOUR ANGER ON ME
ALONE!

666
00:36:55,172 --> 00:36:56,965
I WAS THE ONE
THAT LED THE OTHERS.

667
00:36:56,965 --> 00:36:58,925
I WAS THE ONE THAT SHOT OUT
YOUR MIRROR MACHINE.

668
00:36:58,925 --> 00:37:00,719
AND DID YOU REALLY THINK
THAT WAS THE ONLY MEDIUM

669
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:03,262
OF INSTRUMENTALITY
AT MY COMMAND?

670
00:37:03,262 --> 00:37:05,557
I TOOK THAT CHANCE.

671
00:37:05,557 --> 00:37:07,767
I'M WILLING TO PAY THE PRICE
FOR CHANCING WRONG.

672
00:37:07,767 --> 00:37:09,686
OH, THEN YOU DO ADMIT
TO THE CHARGES?

673
00:37:09,686 --> 00:37:12,105
YES! ANYTHING!

674
00:37:12,105 --> 00:37:15,400
JUST ALLOW THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
TO CONTINUE ITS JOURNEY,

675
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,861
YOU POMPOUS...

676
00:37:17,861 --> 00:37:20,155
IMMATERIAL!

677
00:37:20,155 --> 00:37:21,614
THOSE PEOPLE HAVE DONE YOU
NO HARM.

678
00:37:21,614 --> 00:37:22,532
INADMISSIBLE!

679
00:37:22,532 --> 00:37:23,366
WE'RE LIVING BEINGS,

680
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:25,744
NOT PLAYTHINGS
FOR YOUR AMUSEMENT!

681
00:37:25,744 --> 00:37:28,287
SILENCE!
THIS TRIAL IS OVER!

682
00:37:28,287 --> 00:37:29,164
YOU ARE GUILTY.

683
00:37:29,164 --> 00:37:31,499
ON ALL COUNTS, YOU ARE GUILTY.

684
00:37:31,499 --> 00:37:32,959
AND ACCORDING TO YOUR OWN LAWS,

685
00:37:32,959 --> 00:37:35,921
THIS COURT HAS NO CHOICE
IN FIXING PUNISHMENT.

686
00:37:35,921 --> 00:37:38,131
YOU WILL HANG BY THE NECK,
CAPTAIN,

687
00:37:38,131 --> 00:37:41,801
UNTIL YOU ARE DEAD, DEAD, DEAD!

688
00:37:41,801 --> 00:37:46,890
[ MUSIC ]

689
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:59,360
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STARDATE 2126.3.
FIRST OFFICER SPOCK REPORTING.

690
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:02,363
STILL NO WORD FROM CAPTAIN KIRK
ON THE SURFACE BELOW US.

691
00:38:02,363 --> 00:38:04,323
WAITING TIME IS ALMOST UP.

692
00:38:04,323 --> 00:38:07,326
I WILL SOON BE FORCED
TO ATTEMPT DEPARTURE

693
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:11,998
AS PER INSTRUCTIONS.

694
00:38:16,711 --> 00:38:19,089
UNTIL A MOMENT AGO,
I DIDN'T THINK IT POSSIBLE,

695
00:38:19,089 --> 00:38:19,881
BUT IT WAS.

696
00:38:19,881 --> 00:38:21,800
I DID IT.
I WAS ANGRY.

697
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:25,470
I ACTUALLY EXPERIENCED
GENUINE RAGE.

698
00:38:25,470 --> 00:38:27,889
THIS EXPERIMENT
HAS BEEN SUCCESSFUL.

699
00:38:27,889 --> 00:38:30,349
I'M GLAD
YOU WEREN'T DISAPPOINTED.

700
00:38:30,349 --> 00:38:32,435
WHY, CAPTAIN,
YOU'RE STILL ANGRY.

701
00:38:32,435 --> 00:38:35,730
WOULD THAT I COULD HAVE
SUSTAINED THAT MOMENT.

702
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:39,400
AH, NO MATTER.

703
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:40,735
DO YOU HAVE A LAST REQUEST?

704
00:38:40,735 --> 00:38:42,403
TRELANE, IF YOU THINK
I'M GONNA CHEERFULLY

705
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:45,406
AND OBEDIENTLY STICK MY HEAD
IN THAT NOOSE...

706
00:38:45,406 --> 00:38:50,453
YOU STILL HAVEN'T LEARNED.
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE.

707
00:38:58,586 --> 00:39:00,755
OH, THIS IS BECOMING
QUITE TIRESOME.

708
00:39:00,755 --> 00:39:03,341
IT'S ALL SO VERY EASY.

709
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:07,262
THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM, TRELANE.
EVERYTHING IS EASY.

710
00:39:07,262 --> 00:39:09,764
IT'S GIVING YOU A BAD HABIT.

711
00:39:09,764 --> 00:39:11,308
YOU'RE NOT AWARE OF IT,
BUT YOU HAVE IT.

712
00:39:11,308 --> 00:39:12,309
EH?

713
00:39:12,309 --> 00:39:15,937
YOU DON'T THINK, TRELANE.
THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM.

714
00:39:15,937 --> 00:39:18,815
YOU MISS OPPORTUNITIES
LIKE YOUR ANGER BEFORE

715
00:39:18,815 --> 00:39:20,566
AND MINE RIGHT NOW.

716
00:39:20,566 --> 00:39:22,277
OH, YOU ENJOY IT,

717
00:39:22,277 --> 00:39:24,946
BUT YOU COULDN'T HAVE
ACCOMPLISHED IT WITHOUT ME.

718
00:39:24,946 --> 00:39:26,906
AND YOU KNOW WHY?

719
00:39:26,906 --> 00:39:30,535
BECAUSE YOU'RE A BUMBLING,
INEPT FOOL.

720
00:39:30,535 --> 00:39:31,536
TAKE CARE NOW.

721
00:39:31,536 --> 00:39:32,662
HERE YOU HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY

722
00:39:32,662 --> 00:39:34,873
TO EXPERIENCE SOMETHING
REALLY UNIQUE,

723
00:39:34,873 --> 00:39:36,374
AND YOU'RE WASTING IT.

724
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:38,459
YOU WANNA COMMIT MURDER?
GO AHEAD.

725
00:39:38,459 --> 00:39:42,964
BUT WHERE'S THE SPORT
IN A SIMPLE HANGING?

726
00:39:42,964 --> 00:39:44,674
SPORT?

727
00:39:44,674 --> 00:39:49,012
YES, THE TERROR OF MURDER.

728
00:39:49,012 --> 00:39:52,349
THE SUSPENSE, THE FUN.

729
00:39:52,349 --> 00:39:55,268
OH, I'M INTRIGUED.
GO AHEAD, CAPTAIN.

730
00:39:55,268 --> 00:39:59,689
WHAT DO YOU SUGGEST?

731
00:40:05,904 --> 00:40:08,781
A PERSONAL CONFLICT BETWEEN US.

732
00:40:08,781 --> 00:40:14,120
NOT LIKE THE DUEL BEFORE,
BUT THE REAL THING.

733
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:19,376
THE STAKES?
A HUMAN LIFE, MINE.

734
00:40:19,376 --> 00:40:20,752
[ LAUGHS ]

735
00:40:20,752 --> 00:40:22,254
OH.

736
00:40:22,254 --> 00:40:24,339
YES!
YES!

737
00:40:24,339 --> 00:40:26,091
THAT'S THE IDEA.

738
00:40:26,091 --> 00:40:27,425
OH, THEN YOU APPROVE?

739
00:40:27,425 --> 00:40:31,888
YES!
BUT YOU CAN DO BETTER THAN THAT.

740
00:40:31,888 --> 00:40:35,975
THERE'S STILL NOT ENOUGH SPORT
IN JUST KILLING ME WITH A SWORD.

741
00:40:35,975 --> 00:40:39,396
I KNOW.
THAT WILL BE DULL.

742
00:40:39,396 --> 00:40:42,565
WE'LL HAVE TO HAVE SOMETHING
MORE FANCIFUL.

743
00:40:42,565 --> 00:40:45,193
LET ME SEE.

744
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:50,156
A HUNT, A ROYAL HUNT,
PREDATOR AGAINST PREDATOR.

745
00:40:50,156 --> 00:40:51,783
NOW, YOU MAY GO HIDE
IN THE FOREST,

746
00:40:51,783 --> 00:40:54,411
ANYWHERE YOU LIKE,
AND I SHALL SEEK.

747
00:40:54,411 --> 00:40:57,455
HOW DOES THAT STRIKE YOU,
CAPTAIN?

748
00:40:57,455 --> 00:41:02,377
IT STRIKES ME VERY WELL.

749
00:41:02,377 --> 00:41:06,589
BUT YOU'LL HAVE TO MAKE IT
WORTH MY WHILE, TRELANE.

750
00:41:06,589 --> 00:41:09,550
WHY NOT UP THE STAKES?

751
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:11,052
WHAT STAKES?

752
00:41:11,052 --> 00:41:12,804
YES.

753
00:41:12,804 --> 00:41:17,642
WHILE WE'RE PLAYING OUR GAME,
FREE MY SHIP.

754
00:41:17,642 --> 00:41:19,102
LET IT CONTINUE ON ITS WAY.

755
00:41:19,102 --> 00:41:22,772
IN RETURN, I'LL GIVE YOU
A CONTEST YOU'LL REMEMBER.

756
00:41:22,772 --> 00:41:27,444
ALWAYS BACK TO YOUR SHIP.

757
00:41:27,444 --> 00:41:32,949
OH, WELL, IF IT WILL ADD SPICE
TO THE PURSUIT,

758
00:41:32,949 --> 00:41:38,037
I ACCEPT YOUR TERMS, CAPTAIN.

759
00:41:38,037 --> 00:41:40,457
REMEMBER, YOU MUST TRY
NOT TO LET ME FIND YOU

760
00:41:40,457 --> 00:41:41,958
TOO QUICKLY.

761
00:41:41,958 --> 00:41:44,710
LET ME NOTIFY THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>
THAT IT CAN GO.

762
00:41:44,710 --> 00:41:47,130
AT YOUR CONVENIENCE.

763
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:50,633
[ BEEPING ]

764
00:41:50,633 --> 00:41:53,761
<i>ENTERPRISE, ENTERPRISE,</i> 
THIS IS KIRK.

765
00:41:53,761 --> 00:41:57,765
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

766
00:41:57,765 --> 00:42:01,686
GET THE SHIP AWAY
AS FAST AS YOU CAN.

767
00:42:01,686 --> 00:42:03,646
I'LL TRY AND GIVE YOU THE TIME
YOU NEED.

768
00:42:03,646 --> 00:42:05,857
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

769
00:42:05,857 --> 00:42:15,241
[ MUSIC ]

770
00:42:15,241 --> 00:42:16,784
[ BEEPING ]

771
00:42:16,784 --> 00:42:19,496
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>

772
00:42:19,496 --> 00:42:24,000
CAPTAIN KIRK.

773
00:42:26,002 --> 00:42:34,469
YOU MUST TRY HARDER, CAPTAIN.
THIS IS TOO EASY.

774
00:42:34,469 --> 00:42:35,470
[ BEEPING ]

775
00:42:35,470 --> 00:42:37,013
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>

776
00:42:37,013 --> 00:42:41,976
<i>ENTERPRISE,</i> CAN YOU HEAR ME?

777
00:43:09,254 --> 00:43:11,589
TOUCH, CAPTAIN, TOUCH.

778
00:43:11,589 --> 00:43:13,632
I MUST CONFESS,
YOU SCORED FIRST.

779
00:43:13,632 --> 00:43:19,013
BUT AFTER ALL,
I NEVER PLAYED THIS GAME BEFORE.

780
00:43:19,013 --> 00:43:40,159
AND NOW, LET'S HAVE AT IT AGAIN.

781
00:43:40,159 --> 00:43:57,427
[ LAUGHS ]

782
00:43:57,427 --> 00:43:58,386
[ BEEPING ]

783
00:43:58,386 --> 00:44:03,391
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>

784
00:44:04,725 --> 00:44:09,772
HA! TALLYHO!

785
00:44:19,532 --> 00:44:23,202
AH, YOU MADE A NOBLE FIGHT
OF IT, CAPTAIN.

786
00:44:23,202 --> 00:44:25,330
REMEMBER, TRELANE,
YOU PROMISED TO LET MY SHIP GO.

787
00:44:25,330 --> 00:44:27,332
YES, BUT THIS IS SUCH SPORT.

788
00:44:27,332 --> 00:44:30,668
I MUST FETCH ALL THE OTHERS BACK
TO PLAY.

789
00:44:30,668 --> 00:44:34,880
SO THIS IS VICTORY.
IT HAS A SWEET TASTE.

790
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:38,593
DOWN, CAPTAIN.
ON YOUR KNEES.

791
00:44:38,593 --> 00:44:39,885
YOU HAVEN'T WON, TRELANE.

792
00:44:39,885 --> 00:44:42,138
I HAVE.
I COULD RUN YOU THROUGH.

793
00:44:42,138 --> 00:44:44,015
BUT YOU HAVEN'T WON ANYTHING.

794
00:44:44,015 --> 00:44:46,058
ON YOUR KNEES, CAPTAIN.

795
00:44:46,058 --> 00:44:47,810
NO!

796
00:44:47,810 --> 00:44:50,021
DOES IT STILL TASTE AS SWEET?

797
00:44:50,021 --> 00:44:53,316
I ORDER YOU.
YOU'VE BEEN BEATEN.

798
00:44:53,316 --> 00:44:54,775
BUT I'M NOT DEFEATED.

799
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:59,864
I ORDER YOU. I ORDER YOU.

800
00:44:59,864 --> 00:45:03,075
YOU BROKE MY SWORD.

801
00:45:03,075 --> 00:45:04,785
YOU'VE GOT A LOT TO LEARN
ABOUT WINNING, TRELANE.

802
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:06,412
YOU DARE TO DEFY ME.

803
00:45:06,412 --> 00:45:08,164
IN FACT, YOU'VE GOT A LOT
TO LEARN ABOUT EVERYTHING,

804
00:45:08,164 --> 00:45:11,626
HAVEN'T YOU?

805
00:45:11,626 --> 00:45:14,920
I'LL FIX YOU FOR THAT.
YOU CHEATED.

806
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,506
YOU HAVEN'T PLAYED
THE GAME RIGHT.

807
00:45:16,506 --> 00:45:18,257
I'LL SHOW YOU.

808
00:45:18,257 --> 00:45:22,887
Trelane.

809
00:45:22,887 --> 00:45:27,225
NO!

810
00:45:27,225 --> 00:45:28,476
NO.

811
00:45:28,476 --> 00:45:31,396
YOU SAID I COULD HAVE
THIS PLANET FOR MY VERY OWN.

812
00:45:31,396 --> 00:45:34,065
This has gone far enough.

813
00:45:34,065 --> 00:45:37,109
BUT YOU ALWAYS STOP ME
WHEN I'M HAVING FUN.

814
00:45:37,109 --> 00:45:40,321
You're disobedient and cruel.
We've told you before.

815
00:45:40,321 --> 00:45:42,156
Time to come in now, Trelane.

816
00:45:42,156 --> 00:45:44,576
BUT I DON'T WANNA COME IN,
AND I WON'T.

817
00:45:44,576 --> 00:45:47,203
I'M A GENERAL,
AND I WON'T LISTEN TO YOU.

818
00:45:47,203 --> 00:45:49,830
Enough, Trelane.
Come along.

819
00:45:49,830 --> 00:45:53,585
BUT WHY?
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING WRONG.

820
00:45:53,585 --> 00:45:55,169
I WAS JUST PLAYIN'.

821
00:45:55,169 --> 00:45:57,088
We said come along!

822
00:45:57,088 --> 00:45:59,840
BUT I HAVEN'T STUDYING
MY PREDATORS YET.

823
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:02,009
This is not studying them.

824
00:46:02,009 --> 00:46:04,679
If you cannot take proper care
of your pets,

825
00:46:04,679 --> 00:46:06,472
you cannot have them at all.

826
00:46:06,472 --> 00:46:08,891
BUT I WAS WINNING.
I WAS WINNING.

827
00:46:08,891 --> 00:46:11,768
They're beings, Trelane.
They have spirit.

828
00:46:11,768 --> 00:46:13,020
They're superior.

829
00:46:13,020 --> 00:46:15,772
NO, NO.
YOU SAW.

830
00:46:15,772 --> 00:46:18,693
You'll grow up, Trelane.
You'll understand.

831
00:46:18,693 --> 00:46:20,695
Now, come along.

832
00:46:20,695 --> 00:46:25,199
AW, BUT YOU SAID I COULD.
YOU PROMISED.

833
00:46:25,199 --> 00:46:27,159
I NEVER HAVE ANY FUN.

834
00:46:27,159 --> 00:46:30,329
Stop that nonsense at once,
or you'll not be permitted

835
00:46:30,329 --> 00:46:32,582
to make any more planets.

836
00:46:32,582 --> 00:46:38,504
AW, BUT YOU SAW.
I WAS WINNING.

837
00:46:38,504 --> 00:46:43,008
I WOULD HAVE WON, HONEST.

838
00:46:43,008 --> 00:46:44,636
No, Trelane.

839
00:46:44,636 --> 00:46:46,387
- No, Trelane.

840
00:46:46,387 --> 00:46:51,100
I WOULD HAVE. I WOULD HAVE.
I WOULD HAVE.

841
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:57,982
I WOULD. I WOULD.
I WOULD. I WOULD.

842
00:46:57,982 --> 00:47:00,777
Captain, we regret
that the life paths of yourself

843
00:47:00,777 --> 00:47:05,448
and your companions
have been disturbed.

844
00:47:05,448 --> 00:47:07,950
WHO ARE YOU?
WHO IS TRELANE?

845
00:47:07,950 --> 00:47:09,868
You must forgive our child.

846
00:47:09,868 --> 00:47:12,829
The fault is ours
for indulging him too much.

847
00:47:12,829 --> 00:47:14,415
He will be punished.

848
00:47:14,415 --> 00:47:16,125
We would not have let him
intercept you

849
00:47:16,125 --> 00:47:19,170
had we realized
your vulnerability.

850
00:47:19,170 --> 00:47:21,130
Forgive us, Captain.

851
00:47:21,130 --> 00:47:23,508
We will maintain
your life support conditions

852
00:47:23,508 --> 00:47:25,635
while you return to your ship.

853
00:47:25,635 --> 00:47:30,847
Please accept our apologies.

854
00:47:37,188 --> 00:47:39,273
[ BEEPING ]

855
00:47:39,273 --> 00:47:43,194
CAPTAIN TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>
CAPTAIN TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

856
00:47:43,194 --> 00:47:45,822
Captain, we're receiving you.

857
00:47:45,822 --> 00:47:50,368
BEAM ME UP, MR. SPOCK.
WE'RE FREE TO GO.

858
00:47:50,368 --> 00:47:55,289
[ MUSIC ]

859
00:47:57,291 --> 00:48:00,628
WARPING DOWN, CAPTAIN.
OUR WARP FACTOR, FOUR.

860
00:48:00,628 --> 00:48:02,547
PUSH CHANNELS CLEAR, CAPTAIN.

861
00:48:02,547 --> 00:48:05,675
COLONY BETA SIX CLEARS US
FOR NORMAL APPROACH, SIR.

862
00:48:05,675 --> 00:48:09,804
NORMAL ORBIT
APPROACH PROCEDURES, MR. SULU.

863
00:48:09,804 --> 00:48:10,722
CAPTAIN?

864
00:48:10,722 --> 00:48:12,557
MR. SPOCK,
STILL THINKING ABOUT TRELANE,

865
00:48:12,557 --> 00:48:13,599
IS THAT IT?

866
00:48:13,599 --> 00:48:16,519
FOR THE RECORD, CAPTAIN,
HOW DO WE DESCRIBE HIM?

867
00:48:16,519 --> 00:48:19,104
PURE MENTALITY?
FORCE OF INTELLECT?

868
00:48:19,104 --> 00:48:21,399
EMBODIED ENERGY?
SUPER BEING?

869
00:48:21,399 --> 00:48:24,109
HE MUST BE CLASSIFIED, SIR.

870
00:48:24,109 --> 00:48:26,654
GOD OF WAR, MR. SPOCK.

871
00:48:26,654 --> 00:48:29,240
WELL, I HARDLY
FIND THAT FITTING.

872
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:33,369
THEN A SMALL BOY,
AND A VERY NAUGHTY ONE AT THAT.

873
00:48:33,369 --> 00:48:36,205
IT WILL MAKE A STRANGE ENTRY
IN THE LIBRARY BANKS.

874
00:48:36,205 --> 00:48:37,874
WELL, THEN HE WAS
A VERY STRANGE, SMALL BOY.

875
00:48:37,874 --> 00:48:39,458
ON THE OTHER HAND,
HE WAS PROBABLY DOING THINGS

876
00:48:39,458 --> 00:48:42,461
COMPARABLE TO THE SAME
MISCHIEVOUS PRANKS YOU PLAYED

877
00:48:42,461 --> 00:48:43,962
WHEN YOU WERE A BOY.

878
00:48:43,962 --> 00:48:45,964
MISCHIEVOUS PRANKS, CAPTAIN?

879
00:48:45,964 --> 00:48:50,052
YES, DIPPING LITTLE GIRLS' CURLS
IN INKWELLS,

880
00:48:50,052 --> 00:48:51,679
STEALING APPLES
FROM THE NEIGHBOR'S TREES,

881
00:48:51,679 --> 00:48:56,768
TYING CANS ON--

882
00:48:56,768 --> 00:49:00,730
FORGIVE ME, MR. SPOCK.

883
00:49:00,730 --> 00:49:02,189
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN BETTER.

884
00:49:02,189 --> 00:49:06,943
I SHALL BE DELIGHTED, CAPTAIN.

885
00:49:32,136 --> 00:49:37,099
[ MUSIC ]
